keyFacts: The document is a detailed witness coordination schedule spanning from late November to mid-December, indicating an active legal proceeding.
Logistical notes specify that certain witnesses should not stay at the same hotel as others, suggesting a need for witness separation.
Witnesses include law enforcement (Palm Beach P.D. sergeant), records custodians (birth certificate, AT&T, FedEx, school district), and individuals from various U.S. states.
Locations mentioned include high-profile sites like Mar-a-Lago in Florida and major cities like Los Angeles and New York.
The schedule references FBI personnel (Cart, C20) in New York who are noted as requiring no travel.
